                        Wiley
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v06</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d291</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">291</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-04-21T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.032/4–2149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-21">April 21,
                    1949</date>.</dateline>
                <p>539. Constituent Assembly was convened today by Shah with brief opening
                        address.<note n="1" xml:id="d291fn1">The Majlis passed legislation creating
                        a Senate by a voice vote on May 4 (telegram 607, May 5, from Tehran,
                        891.032/5–549).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
